-- RBC Capital Taps Kriskey as Commodity Investor Sales Head
-- B y   M a r k   S h e n k
-- 2013-09-02T23:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-02/rbc-capital-taps-kriskey-as-commodity-investor-sales-head.html
RBC Capital Markets  hired Kathy Kriskey as head of commodity investor sales in  New York .  Kriskey will be responsible for the company’s commodity
investor business with a focus on commodity index products. She
comes from CIBC, where she was marketing commodity index
products to asset managers, pension plans, endowments and
sovereign wealth funds.  She will report to Bruce Macdonald, the head of commodities
and electronic trading at RBC in New York.  RBC Capital Markets is the investment-banking unit of the
 Royal Bank of Canada . The Montreal-based lender is the country’s
largest bank.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Shenk in New York at 
